    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.25.49-50_0001-2" />
                <note type="curatorial">64-2</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                Skyrim, Rt. 7<lb/>
                Columbia, Mo.<lb/>
                Sep. 22, '59
                    </dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Many thanks for the "amen" attached to Lucile's recent letter! That is the nearest thing to a letter I've received from you since that happy time we four had together on that wonderful trip. <hi rend="underline">Wasn't</hi> it a happy time?!</p>
                
                <p>One of these days I bet you'll write me a whole letter, and I'll be glad.</p>
                
                <p>Yes, our friend, Moffet, has been growing right along.
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.25.49-50_0001b"/>
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                
                I watched him doing it, and at very close range &#8212; about five feet, to be exact!</p>
                
                <p>At present he is off on a wide-ranging trip to the battle-fields of the South. He knows a lot about them already, but he'll know plenty when he gets back! I spent some time on the field of Shiloh, and was so fascinated that I read most of two weeks about the battle after I came home.</p>
                
                <p>By now you are going full-steam ahead out there.
                
                <fw type="curatorial">49</fw>
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.25.49-50_0002a"/>
                <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                
                We began here on Sep. 17, a Thursday. I had feared that my Epic America class might be smaller than usual, but they poured in. Bless them! My Writing of Poetry class is a bit larger than I like, but I can handle it.</p>
                
                <p>We have had the driest summer and fall that I can remember.</p>
                
                <p>Bower, as I have told Lucile, I don't like you too; and
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.25.49-50_0002b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">4</fw>
                    
                    I hope you don't like me the way I don't like you.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                <signed>John N.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">50</fw>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
